.TH "NSYNC" "1" "Mar 06, 2026" "0.12" "mpiFileUtils"
.SH NAME
nsync \- synchronize source and destination in split-mount MPI topologies
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nsync [OPTION] SRC DEST
.SH DESCRIPTION
Parallel MPI application to synchronize SRC to DEST when source and
destination paths are mounted on different node sets.

Unlike dsync, nsync does not require each rank to access both SRC and DEST.
Ranks are assigned as source-side or destination-side workers and data is
transferred over MPI from source owners to destination owners.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-dryrun
Show planned differences and actions without modifying destination.
.TP
.B \-b, \-\-batch\-files N
Process approximately N entries per batch to bound planner memory.
.TP
.B \-D, \-\-delete
Delete extraneous files from destination.
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-contents
Compare regular files by SHA256 digest (instead of size+mtime checks).
.TP
.B \-\-ignore\-symlinks
Ignore symlink entries during sync.
Symlink paths are excluded from scan, compare, and apply stages.
.TP
.B \-\-bufsize SIZE
Set I/O and digest buffer size in bytes.
.TP
.B \-\-imbalance\-threshold R
Batch imbalance ratio threshold for diagnostic warnings.
Defaults to \fB3.0\fP.
.TP
.B \-\-role\-mode MODE
Role assignment mode: \fBauto\fP or \fBmap\fP.
.TP
.B \-\-role\-map SPEC
Explicit role map used with \fB\-\-role\-mode map\fP.
Example: \fB0\-1:src,2\-3:dst\fP.
.TP
.B \-\-trace
Print per-rank stage traces for debugging collectives and pipeline stages.
.TP
.B \-q, \-\-quiet
Quiet output.
Otherwise, progress is printed on the launcher-console log rank
after each batch completes.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print help.
.SH ROLE MODEL
Each rank is assigned one of:

- \fBsrc\fP: can access source path and serves metadata/data from SRC

- \fBdst\fP: can access destination path and applies actions under DEST

In \fBauto\fP mode, nsync probes source readability and destination writability.
In \fBmap\fP mode, roles are assigned directly by world rank.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Synchronize split mounts with automatic role detection:
.B mpirun \-np 2 nsync /src /dst

.TP
Force roles in a shared-mount local test:
.B mpirun \-np 2 nsync \-\-role\-mode map \-\-role\-map 0:src,1:dst /tmp/src /tmp/dst

.TP
Memory-bounded sync with delete and content compare:
.B mpirun \-np 8 nsync \-\-batch\-files 200000 \-\-delete \-\-contents /src /dst
.SH SEE ALSO
dsync(1), dcp(1), dwalk(1), mpifileutils(1)
